## When to re-bootstrap

Re-bootstrap is appropriate when:
- Workflow has shifted significantly (new team, new project phase,
  new tech stack)
- Memory feels stale (stale items piling up, feedback rules contradicting
  each other, tags inconsistent)
- Major life event (job change, role change, returning after long break)

## How to save the answers

Each answer becomes a node in `nodes/`:

| Question topic | Suggested node name |
|---|---|
| Workflow style | `feedback_workflow.md` or `user_workflow_style.md` |
| Testing preference | `feedback_testing.md` |
| Code review process | `project_code_review.md` |
| Sensitive areas | `project_sensitive_areas.md` |
| Decision history | `project_<topic>_history.md` for each |
| Communication when wrong | `feedback_correction_handling.md` |
| Time pressure | `feedback_urgency_signals.md` |
| Scope discipline | `feedback_scope_discipline.md` |
{% if status_mcp == 'teams' or tickets_mcp == 'odoo' %}| Automation identity | `user_identity.md` (already exists — replace placeholders) |
{% endif %}

Follow [[conventions_node_format]] for the body structure
(`**Why:**` + `**How to apply:**` for feedback/project nodes).

After saving the new nodes, also update `MEMORY.md` index — add a one-line
entry under the appropriate type section (Feedback / Project / User).

